# 📡 AethelFrame Async Job State Webhook Specification

This specification defines the event-driven notification layer for tracking asynchronous pipeline jobs. It aligns with **CloudEvents 1.0**, enforces cryptographic delivery security, and provides deterministic state reconciliation to replace HTTP polling in CI/CD and production environments.

---

## 🔄 Job State Machine & Event Taxonomy

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> job.created
  job.created --> job.queued
  job.queued --> stage.started
  stage.started --> job.progress
  job.progress --> stage.completed
  stage.completed --> stage.started
  stage.completed --> job.completed
  stage.started --> job.failed
  job.completed --> [*]
  job.failed --> [*]
  job.queued --> job.cancelled
  job.cancelled --> [*]
  job.queued --> job.expired
  job.expired --> [*]
  
  note right of job.progress
    Throttled: max 1 event / 10s
    Contains: current_stage, progress_pct, eta_sec
  end note
  
  note right of job.failed
    Contains: error_code, error_message, stack_trace_id, recovery_suggestion
  end note
```

| Event Type | Trigger Condition | Data Payload Focus |
|------------|-------------------|-------------------|
| `job.created` | Payload validated & job ID issued | `job_id`, `project_id`, `estimated_duration_sec` |
| `job.queued` | Job assigned to worker pool | `queue_depth`, `worker_tier`, `priority` |
| `stage.started` | Engine enters new pipeline phase | `stage_name`, `stage_params`, `start_timestamp` |
| `job.progress` | Throttled metric emission (max $1/10\text{s}$) | `current_stage`, `progress_pct`, `eta_sec` |
| `stage.completed` | Pipeline phase finishes successfully | `stage_name`, `stage_duration_sec`, `output_artifacts` |
| `job.completed` | Final artifact ready & signed | `artifacts`, `c2pa_manifest_url`, `total_duration_sec` |
| `job.failed` | Unrecoverable error in any stage | `error_code`, `error_message`, `failed_stage`, `recovery_suggestion` |
| `job.cancelled` | User/API revocation or TTL breach | `cancelled_by`, `reason`, `partial_artifacts` |
| `job.expired` | Job exceeded `max_queue_wait` | `expires_at`, `cleanup_status` |

