## 🔐 Security, Idempotency & Delivery Guarantees

### HTTP Headers
| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Aethel-Id` | Unique event ID (matches `id` in envelope) |
| `X-Aethel-Timestamp` | Unix epoch (seconds) of generation |
| `X-Aethel-Signature` | `v1=sha256=<hex_hmac>` |
| `X-Aethel-Retry-Count` | Number of delivery attempts ($0 \dots 5$) |

### Signature Verification Algorithm
```text
payload_body = raw HTTP body string (UTF-8)
timestamp = X-Aethel-Timestamp
secret = webhook signing secret

string_to_sign = timestamp + "." + payload_body
expected_sig = HMAC-SHA256(string_to_sign, secret)
```
**Replay Protection:** Reject if `|current_time - timestamp| > 300` seconds.  
**Timing-Safe Comparison:** Always use constant-time equality for signature validation.

### Delivery & Retry Policy
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| **Success** | `200–299` or `300–399` → Mark delivered |
| **Client Error** | `400–499` → **Drop immediately**, log to audit trail |
| **Server Error** | `5xx` or timeout → Exponential backoff: $1\text{m} \to 5\text{m} \to 15\text{m} \to 1\text{h} \to 6\text{h}$ |
| **Max Retries** | 5 attempts → Move to Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) for 30 days |
| **Idempotency** | Cache processed `X-Aethel-Id` for $24\text{h}$. Ignore duplicates. Return `200` immediately. |

